After generating, always validate:

```bash
python /mnt/skills/public/docx/scripts/office/validate.py {{FILENAME}}_Executive_Briefing.docx
```

## Key Patterns

### Options Table

Each row in the options table uses this structure. The recommended option gets `accentCellShading` on all cells and a `"\u2713 RECOMMENDED"` label:

```javascript
new TableRow({
  children: [
    new TableCell({ borders, width: { size: 560, type: WidthType.DXA }, margins: cellMargins,
      shading: isRecommended ? accentCellShading : undefined,
      children: [new Paragraph({ children: [new TextRun({ text: "A", font: "Arial", size: 20, bold: true, color: CS_ORANGE })] })] }),
    new TableCell({ borders, width: { size: 2200, type: WidthType.DXA }, margins: cellMargins,
      shading: isRecommended ? accentCellShading : undefined,
      children: [
        new Paragraph({ children: [new TextRun({ text: optionName, font: "Arial", size: 20, bold: true, color: CS_DARK })] }),
        // Only for recommended:
        ...(isRecommended ? [new Paragraph({ spacing: { before: 60 }, children: [
          new TextRun({ text: "\u2713 RECOMMENDED", font: "Arial", size: 18, bold: true, color: CS_ORANGE })
        ] })] : []),
      ] }),
    // ... description and assessment cells
  ]
})
```

### Objection Pairs

Use the `objectionPair()` helper. It returns an array of two paragraphs, so spread it:

```javascript
...objectionPair(
  "\u201CCustomer's exact concern in their voice.\u201D",
  "Empathetic but firm response with specific evidence."
),
```

### Timeline Table

Standard two-column table with dark header:

```javascript
new Table({
  width: { size: 9360, type: WidthType.DXA },
  columnWidths: [3200, 6160],
  rows: [
    // Header
    new TableRow({ children: [
      new TableCell({ borders, width: { size: 3200, type: WidthType.DXA }, shading: headerCellShading, margins: cellMargins,
        children: [new Paragraph({ children: [new TextRun({ text: "Milestone", font: "Arial", size: 20, bold: true, color: "FFFFFF" })] })] }),
      new TableCell({ borders, width: { size: 6160, type: WidthType.DXA }, shading: headerCellShading, margins: cellMargins,
        children: [new Paragraph({ children: [new TextRun({ text: "Target", font: "Arial", size: 20, bold: true, color: "FFFFFF" })] })] }),
    ] }),
    // Data rows...
  ]
})
```
